This directory is populated at install time by fetch-webview2.ps1.

Run from the desktop/windows/ directory (or via install.py):

    powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File fetch-webview2.ps1

Files placed here by the script:
    net45/Microsoft.Web.WebView2.Core.dll
    net45/Microsoft.Web.WebView2.WinForms.dll
    runtimes/win-x64/native/WebView2Loader.dll   (if present in the package)
    runtimes/win-arm64/native/WebView2Loader.dll  (if present)

These are the vendored .NET Framework (net45) builds of the WebView2 managed
SDK, required because the widget host (cognitive-stress.ps1) targets Windows
PowerShell 5.1 (.NET Framework), not PowerShell 7 / .NET Core.

The binaries are NOT committed to git — they are fetched from NuGet at install
time. The fetch script pins a specific version for reproducible installs.

The DLLs themselves make no network calls; they are only loaded by the widget
host (cognitive-stress.ps1), which is private and makes no network calls at
runtime.
